An investor group led by ConistonPartners said it plans to continue its effort to gain controlof Allegis Corp despite the defensive maneuvers Allegisannounced last week.    Allegis said then that it would borrow three billion dlrsand pay shareholders a dividend of 60 dlrs per share, loweringthe company's net worth. The Coniston group, which owns 13 pctof Allegis stock, has said that it would seek shareholderconsents to remove 13 of the 16 Allegis directors. The grouphad said it would consider breaking up Allegis into itsairline, hotel and vehicle rental components if it succeeded.    The Coniston group said it expects to make a furtherannouncement today on its plans for Allegis.    Wall Street analysts and traders had not expected Conistonto abandon its pursuit of Allegis as a result of the Allegisdefensive measures.    Allegis officials were unavailable for comment. Reuter&#3;